1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:04,800
What if I told you some creatures wear the same dangerous costume?

2
00:00:04,800 --> 00:00:09,200
This is called Mullerian mimicry—where harmful species share similar warning signals.

3
00:00:09,200 --> 00:00:11,200
This strategy benefits them all.

4
00:00:11,200 --> 00:00:14,000
Predators learn to avoid their shared colors!

5
00:00:14,000 --> 00:00:14,400
Examples?

6
00:00:14,400 --> 00:00:19,200
Think of butterflies, wasps, and even some frogs—all sharing bright warning patterns.

7
00:00:19,200 --> 00:00:22,400
But here's the twist—this mimicry isn't always perfect.

8
00:00:22,400 --> 00:00:24,000
Uncertainty lurks in nature!

9
00:00:24,000 --> 00:00:26,000
Curious for more science secrets?

10
00:00:26,000 --> 00:00:30,000
Hit that like button and follow for the next mystery!
